resultVideos.Title: Jorma Sipilä: Onko julkisten palveluiden yksityistäminen uhka universalismille?
resultVideos.Description:
"Julkisten palveluiden yksityistäminen ei ole vaarallista, jos se pysyy valtion hanskassa", emeritusprofessori Jorma Sipilä sanoo.

Taustalla olevan valtion tulee olla demokraattinen ja hallita kokonaisuutta.

"Tällä hetkellä elinkeinoelämä kuitenkin uhkaa ottaa pyöritettäväkseen valtiolle kuuluvat toiminnat, ja valtion ote irtoaa", Sipilä pohtii.

Sipilän mukaan suunta on kohti mallia, jossa palveluita tuotetaan vain niille, kenellä on rahaa.

"Tällöin universalismi kyllä katoaa."

Valtion aseman vahvuus määrittää pitkälti, miten julkisten palveluiden yksityistäminen vaikuttaa universalismiin.

_____________________________________________

Video on osa Vastavuoroinen sosiaalityö -kirjaan liittyvää virtuaaliseminaaria, jossa kirjan kirjoittajat avaavat näkemyksiään sosiaalityöhön liittyvistä ajankohtaisista kysymyksistä.

Kirja on syntynyt osana Suomen Akatemian rahoittamaa "Reciprocal Relationships and the Construction of Well-being During Critical Periods of Everyday Life" -tutkimushanketta.

resultVideos.Description:
Eduskunnan käsittelyssä osana maakuntauudistusta oleva kasvupalvelulaki avaa toteutuessaan työvoimapalvelut yksityisille markkinoille. Koska maakuntauudistuksen tulevaisuus on epävarma, hallitus antoi torstaina eduskunnalle erillisen kiireellisen lakiesityksen työllisyyspalveluiden yksityistämisestä. Kansanedustajamme Hanna Sarkkinen kysyikin kyselytunnilla työministeri Lindströmiltä:

-Onko työllisyyspalveluiden yksityistäminen niin kiireellinen tavoite, että se pitää tuoda kiireellisellä uudistuksesta erillisellä lakiesityksellä eduskuntaan?

recommandationVideos.Title: Tohmajärveltä taistellen Syvärille 1941
recommandationVideos.Description:
Jalkaväkirykmentti 9. perustettiin kesäkuussa 1941 Kontiolahdessa 9. prikaatin varusmiehistä ja Pohjois-Karjalan suojeluskuntapiirin reservijoukoista. Rykmentti liitettiin eversti Antero Svenssonin 7. divisioonaan yhdessä jalkaväkirykmenttien 30 ja 51 kanssa. 
Karjalan Armeijan joukko-osastot etenivät valtakunnanrajan yli vanhaan Suomen karjalaan 10. heinäkuuta kello 17.00 alkaen. Eteneminen vanhan Suomen Karjalan alueella jatkui rankkojen taistelujen saattelemana aina Sortavalaan saakka, jonne saavuttiin 15. elokuuta 1941.
Etenemistä jatkettiin 23. elokuuta Koivuselkään ja siletä edelleen Uomaan kylään. Elokuun lopussa 1941 rykmentti ylitti vanhan rajan Käsnäselän ja Kolatselän välissä. Jalkaväkirykmentti yhdeksän taisteli syyskuussa Aunukseen kuuluvissa Nirkan, Pyhäjärven, Kaskanan ja Latvan erämaissa lokakuun alkuun saakka. 
Syvärin joki ylitettiin 6. lokakuuta 1941 kolmannella yrityskerralla. Marraskuussa 1941 eteneminen päättyi Ostan, Goran ja Horomovitsin linjalle. Näissä asemissa Jalkaväkirykmentti yhdeksän oli kesään 1944 saakka.
Tällä videolla kerron kesän ja syksyn 1941 JR 9:n taisteluista Tohmajärveltä aina Syvärin taakse Levinaan ja Baranyn takaisiin kyliin saakka.  Lähteenä tällä videolla olen käyttänyt sotapäiväkirjoja ja kolmea 2010-luvulla tekemiäni sotakirjoja. Kirjojen tekemisen taustalla oli isäni ja hänen neljä veljeä, jotka palvelivat koko sodan ajan Jalkaväkirykementti yhdeksän eri pataljoonissa.
Isäni toimi jatkosodan aikana II/JR 9 konekiväärimiehenä. Hänen esimiehenä oli lähes koko sodan ajan Mannerheim-ristin ritari Ahti Vuorensola.

recommandationVideos.Title: Jussi Halla-aho | IS Vaaligrilli 19.1. | Presidentinvaalit 2024
recommandationVideos.Description:
Presidenttiehdokas Jussi Halla-aho vieraili Ilta-Sanomien vaaligrillissä. Hanna Vesala haastattelee.

* Tekstitykset saa auki videon asetuksista *

Presidentinvaaleja koskevat mielipidemittaukset:

0:00 Aloitus. Olette nostaneet eniten kannatusta tuoreimmassa kannatusmittauksessa. Onko vaalipäivänä tulossa tsunami äänimäärän suhteen?
0:39 Missä koette onnistuneenne, koska gallup-luvut ovat nousussa?
1:02 Mittausten mukaan teillä ei olisi toisella kierroksella mitään mahdollisuuksia ketään vastaan. Millainen ongelma tämä on kampanjallenne ja miksi teitä sitten kannattaa äänestää?

Perussuomalaisten riveistä tulleet avaukset ja vastuut puheista:

2:13 Perussuomalaisten riveistä on hyvin lyhyesä ajassa muun muassa vihjattu apulaisoikeuskanslerin potkuilla, puhuttu ay-liikkeestä mafiana ja pohdittu ulkoministeriön protestikirjeen lähettäjien tulevaisuutta. Hyväksyttekö tällaiset ulostulot?
5:33 Perussuomalaista on myös haastettu miksi emme saaneet gallupeja pitkään aikaan. Onko kyseessä amerikkalaistyylinen salaliittojen levittäminen?
7:11 Yhdysvaltain entisen presidentin on katsottu yllyttäneen väkijoukkoja vallankaappausyritykseen. Hyväksyittekö te silloin tämän Trumpin toiminnan. Onko poliittisilla johtajilla vastuu siitä mitä he puhuvat?

Venäjä-mieliseen ryhmään liittyminen eurovaalien 2019 jälkeen:

9:36 TV-mainoksen mukaan olette olleet aina oikeassa. Kuitenkin vuoden 2019 eurovaalien jälkeen puolueenne liittyi Venäjä-mieliseen ryhmään. Miten selitätte tämän?
11:58 Eli maahanmuuttokriittokriittisyys ajoi Venäjä-mielisyyden ylitse Europarlamenttiryhmään liittymisen kriteereissä?

Kehitysyhteistyöstä leikkaaminen:

12:30 Suomen nykyinen hallitus leikkaa kehitysyhteistyöstä. Kenellekään ei ole salaisuus että perussuomalaiset tukevat näitä leikkauksia. Miten nämä ovat perusteltavissa tilanteessa jossa uusikin presidentti joutuu käymään taistelua sieluista siinä kuka kenenkin leiriin kuuluu länsi vs. autoritääriset johtajat -tilanteessa?
14:07 Pekka Haaviston mukaan nämä leikkaukset heikentävät Suomen ulkopolitiikkaa ja mahdollisuuksia vaikuttaa, te ette ole tästä huolissanne?

Ulkopoliittinen linja Venäjän ja Kiinan osalta:

14:48 Jaatteko sen näkemyksen että teitä voisi ulkopoliittiselta linjaltanne kutsua haukaksi?
15:43 Puhutte Venäjästä saalistajavaltiona. Miten teidän mielestänne pitää estää Kiinan ja Venäjän vaikutusvallan kasvamista Afrikassa?
16:57 Oletteko presidenttiehdokas Stubbin kanssa samaa mieltä että Kiinaa ei voi laittaa samalle pahan akselille Venäjän, Iranin ja Pohjois-Korean kanssa?
17:36 Millä aikataululla teidän mielestä pitäisi katkaista suhteita Kiinaan? Tarkoittaako se kaupan katkaisua?

Venäjän kaksoiskansalaiset Suomessa:

18:24 Ilta-Sanomien vaalitentissä tiistaina 16.1. olitte muun muassa Stubbin kanssa linjalla että kaksoiskansalaisuus tulisi poistaa myös taannehtivasti Venäjän kansalaisilta Suomessa. Miten te tämän käytännössä aikoisitte hoitaa ja mitä seurauksia sillä voisi olla?
19:23 Mikäli Suomi ryhtyisi tähän kaksoiskansalaisuus-operaatioon, käyttäisikö Venäjä sitä propagandana että sorramme venäläisiä ja Venäjän täytyy tulla avustamaan?
20:33 Jos Venäjä aloittaa tällaisen propagandakampanjan. Kuinka meidän tulee vastata?

Presidentin neuvonantajaryhmä & armahdusoikeus:

21:26 Olette sanoneet kantanne muodostuvan lähinnä oman päänne sisällä eikä teillä ole mitään erityistä sparrausrinkiä. Millaisen tiimin te rakentaisitte presidenttinä ympärillenne?
22:06 Miten presidenttinä käyttäisitte armahdusoikeuttanne? Olisitteko tiukka vai laajemmalla skaalalla?
23:33 Presidentillä on ollut Suomessa tapana edistää ilmastonmuutoksen vastaista työtä. Miten te toimisitte tässä presidenttinä?

Ämpärikysymykset:

24:52 Minkä biisin tahdissa olisit halunnut tulla sisään tähän tenttiin?
25:15 Minkä biisin vedät karaokessa jos on pakko laulaa?
25:39 Ketä kotimaista poliitikkoa ihailet?
26:14 Pelkäätkö ihmisiin luottamista?
26:41 Miten kierrätys näkyy arjessasi?

Lähde ja uutinen: "Halla-aholta selkeä linjaus: 'Totta kai siitä täytyy leikata ja siitä täytyy leikata ensimmäisenä'" / Ilta-Sanomat

https://www.is.fi/politiikka/art-2000010130010.html

recommandationVideos.Title: Tohmajärveltä taistellen Syvärille 1941
recommandationVideos.Description:
Jalkaväkirykmentti 9. perustettiin kesäkuussa 1941 Kontiolahdessa 9. prikaatin varusmiehistä ja Pohjois-Karjalan suojeluskuntapiirin reservijoukoista. Rykmentti liitettiin eversti Antero Svenssonin 7. divisioonaan yhdessä jalkaväkirykmenttien 30 ja 51 kanssa. 
Karjalan Armeijan joukko-osastot etenivät valtakunnanrajan yli vanhaan Suomen karjalaan 10. heinäkuuta kello 17.00 alkaen. Eteneminen vanhan Suomen Karjalan alueella jatkui rankkojen taistelujen saattelemana aina Sortavalaan saakka, jonne saavuttiin 15. elokuuta 1941.
Etenemistä jatkettiin 23. elokuuta Koivuselkään ja siletä edelleen Uomaan kylään. Elokuun lopussa 1941 rykmentti ylitti vanhan rajan Käsnäselän ja Kolatselän välissä. Jalkaväkirykmentti yhdeksän taisteli syyskuussa Aunukseen kuuluvissa Nirkan, Pyhäjärven, Kaskanan ja Latvan erämaissa lokakuun alkuun saakka. 
Syvärin joki ylitettiin 6. lokakuuta 1941 kolmannella yrityskerralla. Marraskuussa 1941 eteneminen päättyi Ostan, Goran ja Horomovitsin linjalle. Näissä asemissa Jalkaväkirykmentti yhdeksän oli kesään 1944 saakka.
Tällä videolla kerron kesän ja syksyn 1941 JR 9:n taisteluista Tohmajärveltä aina Syvärin taakse Levinaan ja Baranyn takaisiin kyliin saakka.  Lähteenä tällä videolla olen käyttänyt sotapäiväkirjoja ja kolmea 2010-luvulla tekemiäni sotakirjoja. Kirjojen tekemisen taustalla oli isäni ja hänen neljä veljeä, jotka palvelivat koko sodan ajan Jalkaväkirykementti yhdeksän eri pataljoonissa.

recommandationVideos.Title: Ylituoton vuosi 2023 – Sifter-rahasto  31%
recommandationVideos.Description:
Sifter-rahasto suoriutui vuonna 2023 erinomaisesti, tuottaen 31 % (R/I-luokka). Vuoden alussa maailman talouden epävarmuus oli suuri ja harvat odottivat osakemarkkinoilta suuria. Vuoden aikana inflaatio laski kuitenkin nopeasti korkojen nostojen myötä. Myös tekoälyn aiheuttama innostus nosti erityisesti Yhdysvaltain ja teknologiasektorin osakkeita.

Kaikki yhtiöt tai osakkeet eivät kuitenkaan ole pärjänneet yhtä hyvin. Viime vuodet ovat suosineet erityisesti niitä yhtiöitä, joilla on vahva tase, hinnoitteluvoimaa sekä kasvupotentiaalia.

Maailmanlaajuinen, tarkasti valittu laatuyhtiöiden joukko on mahdollistanut sen, että Sifter-rahasto on ylittänyt useimmat indeksit myös kuluneena vuonna. 

Videolla käymme läpi miten Sifter-rahaston vuosi 2023 meni. Sifterin portfolio managerit jakavat ajatuksia salkkuyhtiöistä.

recommandationVideos.Title: Making OLED Displays
recommandationVideos.Description:
Skip to 10:40 if you just want to see how they were made. 

Contents:
0:00 Intro
1:29 First OLED: Tang and van Slyke
2:56 Polymer LEDs
4:25 Principle of the AlQ3 OLED
10:40 Let's make some OLEDs!
11:00 3D-printer photolithography 
13:30 Physical Vapor Deposition (PVD)
15:52 Device operation
16:57 Black spot formation/degradation
18:50 Hermetic encapsulation

All technical details described in this video can currently be found in the public domain.

Video on the inventors of the OLED: 
"Pioneers of OLED: The Ching Wan Tang and Steven Van Slyke Story" 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dbt8cGQPcpg

The original paper by Tang and van Slyke can be downloaded for $35 from:
https://aip.scitation.org/doi/pdf/10.1063/1.98799.
I did not do this, so I hope my memory served me well...

Other sources used (fair use policy assumed):
Photo flexible OLED-display: pi-scale.eu
Photo plasma display: "History of the Plasma Display Panel" by Larry F Weber,
Photo Atari Lynx: boards.dingoonity.org/retro-gaming/atari-lynx-lcd-mod-by-mcwill/
Photo PVD: https://www.tekniker.es/en/pvd
Did I forget anyone / objections? Please let me know and I'll set it straight.

ITO substrates can be bought from many different suppliers on Ebay.com, with widely varying prices. I bought mine (5 pieces) from seller "yaolihong2013" (no affiliation) because the same shop also sells Ytterbium.

The AlQ3 and TPD were both bought from TCI-chemicals (no affiliation).

The 3D-printer used for the photoresist exposures was a Phrozen Sonic Mini 4K. Avoid the new update (1.9) of the Chitubox-software supplied with this printer because it does not work properly. Version 1.8 or earlier does works correctly.

Photoresist used : AZ 4533 supplied by Microchemicals (no affiliation)

Do you like what I do and want to support it? I'v recently started a patreon page: https://www.patreon.com/huygens_optics

recommandationVideos.Title: Tohmajärveltä taistellen Syvärille 1941
recommandationVideos.Description:
Jalkaväkirykmentti 9. perustettiin kesäkuussa 1941 Kontiolahdessa 9. prikaatin varusmiehistä ja Pohjois-Karjalan suojeluskuntapiirin reservijoukoista. Rykmentti liitettiin eversti Antero Svenssonin 7. divisioonaan yhdessä jalkaväkirykmenttien 30 ja 51 kanssa. 
Karjalan Armeijan joukko-osastot etenivät valtakunnanrajan yli vanhaan Suomen karjalaan 10. heinäkuuta kello 17.00 alkaen. Eteneminen vanhan Suomen Karjalan alueella jatkui rankkojen taistelujen saattelemana aina Sortavalaan saakka, jonne saavuttiin 15. elokuuta 1941.
Etenemistä jatkettiin 23. elokuuta Koivuselkään ja siletä edelleen Uomaan kylään. Elokuun lopussa 1941 rykmentti ylitti vanhan rajan Käsnäselän ja Kolatselän välissä. Jalkaväkirykmentti yhdeksän taisteli syyskuussa Aunukseen kuuluvissa Nirkan, Pyhäjärven, Kaskanan ja Latvan erämaissa lokakuun alkuun saakka. 
Syvärin joki ylitettiin 6. lokakuuta 1941 kolmannella yrityskerralla. Marraskuussa 1941 eteneminen päättyi Ostan, Goran ja Horomovitsin linjalle. Näissä asemissa Jalkaväkirykmentti yhdeksän oli kesään 1944 saakka.
Tällä videolla kerron kesän ja syksyn 1941 JR 9:n taisteluista Tohmajärveltä aina Syvärin taakse Levinaan ja Baranyn takaisiin kyliin saakka.  Lähteenä tällä videolla olen käyttänyt sotapäiväkirjoja ja kolmea 2010-luvulla tekemiäni sotakirjoja. Kirjojen tekemisen taustalla oli isäni ja hänen neljä veljeä, jotka palvelivat koko sodan ajan Jalkaväkirykementti yhdeksän eri pataljoonissa.
Isäni toimi jatkosodan aikana II/JR 9 konekiväärimiehenä. Hänen esimiehenä oli lähes koko sodan ajan Mannerheim-ristin ritari Ahti Vuorensola.

recommandationVideos.Title: Mitä odottaa vuodelta 2024?
recommandationVideos.Description:
Halusin tehdä videon tämän alkavan vuoden energioihin liittyen. Mitä vuosi 2024 tuo mukanaan, ja millaisia muutoksia se merkitsee sekä yksilötasolla että kollektiivisella tasolla?

Olen tuntenut syvästi, että vuodet 2023 ja 2024 ovat eräänlainen parivaljakko. Numerologisesti katsottuna vuosi 2023 edusti numeroa 7, joka on feminiininen luku. Vuosi 2023 oli syvän sisäisen työskentelyn, rauhoittumisen ja puhdistautumisen aikaa. 

Vuosi 2024 edustaa puolestaan numeroa 8, joka on hyvin maskuliininen luku. Tänä vuonna on aika siirtyä tuomaan käytännön tasolle viime vuoden aikana opittua ja sisäistettyä tietoa. Numero 8 on myös karman luku, joten nyt pääset niittämään kylvämääsi satoa.

Tämä vuosi pyytää sinua olemaan aktiivinen toimija, sekä oman todellisuutesi, että kollektiivisen todellisuuden rakentajana. Miten ottaa ohjakset omiin käsiin, ja lähteä rakentamaan tästä elämäsi parasta vuotta?

recommandationVideos.Title: Stock market today: US stocks fall as rate-cut bets get a reality check | January 17, 2024
recommandationVideos.Description:
#stocks  #inflation #YahooFinance #recession #bitcoin #Biden #Stockmarket #coronavirus #memestocks #Fed #YahooFinance #investing #stockmarket #crypto 

To get the latest market news check out finance.yahoo.com

U.S. stocks fell on Wednesday to signal no letup in a rough January, as investors' optimism for interest rate cuts got a reality check and worries grew about China's economy.

The Dow Jones Industrial Average (^DJI) fell 0.3%, while the S&P 500 (^GSPC) slid 0.7%, set to build on Tuesday's losing start to the holiday-shortened week. The Nasdaq Composite (^IXIC) was down roughly 1.1%.

Stocks have struggled as policymakers push back against persistent bets that central banks will cut rates early and often in 2024. ECB president Christine Lagarde on Wednesday joined the likes of Federal Reserve governor Chris Waller in warning that expectations of imminent loosening are too high.

Another knock back came from disappointing GDP data, suggesting that China's growth is flagging despite stimulus measures. Oil prices fell amid fears of a pullback in demand from the world's second-biggest economy.

Also out Wednesday, the December retail sales report showed consumer spending remains resilient. Retail sales grew 0.6% in December, according to Census Bureau data. Economists had expected a 0.4% increase, according to Bloomberg data.

Regional bank fourth quarter results are in focus in the morning after earnings from Wall Street's big lenders got a mixed reception.

recommandationVideos.Title: Salesforce CEO on how AI is shaping the future
recommandationVideos.Description:
Reporting from the World Economic Forum, in Davos, Switzerland, Yahoo Finance’s Brian Sozzi holds a wide-ranging discussion on artificial intelligence with Salesforce (CRM) CEO Marc Benioff, who says AI “can make people a lot better."
Benioff outlines an Italian Gucci call center case showing AI systems boosting worker productivity and revenue by 30%. By handling routine requests, the technology-enabled employees to become more versatile “Gucci everything agents” — demonstrating the potential to spawn "digital people" rather than prompt replacement.
However, Benioff warns of rising threats like misinformation and data theft rendering AI “a creator of inequality," saying access to transparent, accountable AI should constitute “a human right." With minimal governmental AI oversight currently, he presses regulators to “take this really seriously” in 2024 given deployment is accelerating rapidly.
On healthcare, Benioff shares a personal example of AI analyzing his cardiac CT, making world-class diagnostics accessible to general practitioners globally. While he notes the tech "is not perfect," he says its democratization promises wider care gains just by implementing artificial intelligence.
Benioff also discusses climate change efforts, stressing his belief that businesses can simultaneously chase profits and purpose through sustainability. He argues that by innovating around problems like emissions and biodiversity, “business can be the greatest platform for change” and that "business doesn't have to be just business, it can be about improving the world."
It's all part of Yahoo Finance's exclusive coverage from the World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland, where our team will speak to top decision-makers as well as preeminent leaders in business, finance, and politics about the world’s most pressing issues and priorities for the coming year.

recommandationVideos.Description:
Around 30,000 people were infected with HIV and hepatitis C through contaminated blood products in the 1970s and 1980s. Campaigners say that one person affected by the scandal dies every four days. The final report has been postponed until May. 

We speak with Louise Huxley, whose brother Peter Lloyd, received a blood transfusion in 1985 after a car accident. Peter received a letter dated 6 November 1995, ten years later, from the National Blood Transfusion Service saying he may have received infected blood. Her brother Peter Lloyd was 55 when he died of liver cancer as a result of Hep C.

recommandationVideos.Title: India's Infra Thrust To Ladakh: Countering China & Pakistan
recommandationVideos.Description:
India’s military is in the fourth winter of its advanced forward deployment against China’s People’s Liberation Army (PLA) forces along the Line of Actual Control (LAC) in eastern Ladakh. China’s renewed aggression in 2020 led to the deadly Galwan clashes in June that year, with the consequent military buildup and standoff. Both sides continue to engage at the military, diplomatic and political level. But the shattering of trust, protocols and agreements means India is on perpetual guard in the present while ramping up its preparedness for the future.

StratNews Global’s team of Amitabh P. Revi, Rohit Pandita and Karan Marwaha travels along alpine altitudes through the frozen desert landscape in eastern Ladakh and Siachen to bring you this series: The Himalayan Frontier. These ground reports document the sustained infrastructure push in road connectivity and air bridges, record substantial progress in alternate axes that are in play and are being planned, and capture on camera how the Indian Army, the Border Roads Organisation (BRO) and the Indian Air Force’s women, men and machines are honing their all-weather readiness during another winter, against the two-front threat from China and Pakistan.

In this episode, we travel from Manali, through the Atal Tunnel under the Rohtang Pass and drive on the Darcha-Padam-Nimmu (NPD) road to Leh. This is a crucial third axis to Leh that will ensure all-weather connectivity for India's military and civilians, even when upto fifteen foot high snow walls usually close passes as high as 17,000  feet for months in the winter. The Border Roads Organisation (BRO) is the nodal agency for this infrastructural push and we travel with their personnel to understand their engineering achievements through bone-chilling alpine altitudes, how they drill through mountain ranges, lay bridges across fast-moving rivers and the challenges at these heights, temperatures and topographies.

#Ladakh #ChinaPakistanThreat #BorderRoads #LAC #IndiaChinaBorder #AtalTunnel #RohtangPass #NPDRoad #BorderRoadsOrganisation #PLA #GalwanClashes

Raidījumā var būt iekļauta produktu izvietošana, iespējams tiek lietoti necenzēti vārdi, alkohols un smēķēts. Atgādinām: alkohola, tabakas un nikotīna izstrādājumu lietošanai ir negatīva ietekme uz veselību, šo produktu pārdošana, iegādāšanās un nodošana nepilngadīgām personām ir aizliegta.
 
Raidījuma veidotāji lūdz ņemt vērā, ka pausts tiek tikai un vienīgi viņu personīgais viedoklis, kas izriet no publiskā telpā pieejamās informācijas. Atvainojamies, ja raidījuma laikā esam kādu aizskāruši ar pateikto.

recommandationVideos.Title: Why The World Is Rushing Back To The Moon
recommandationVideos.Description:
During the Cold War, competition between the the United States and the former USSR was fierce, as the two countries rallied for the chance to make history by getting to the moon first. In 1959, the Soviet Union beat the U.S. to become the first nation to reach the surface of the moon with its Luna 2 spacecraft. But, the United States was the first country to put man on the moon in 1969, and to this day is still the only nation to have landed people on the moon. To date, only five nations, the U.S., Russia, China, Japan and India, have completed a successful soft landing on the moon. But bolstered by evidence of the presence of water and other natural resources, many more nations and private companies are now seeking to get to the moon. And whoever is able to establish a significant lunar presence first could have big implications on Earth as well as the cosmos.

recommandationVideos.Title: Perspective: AI in Education | 20 April, 2023
recommandationVideos.Description:
Technology has always played an important role in education but its current use is more prevalent than ever thanks to the increased availability of smart devices and web-based curriculum. A new dimension has been added with advances in the field of Artificial Intelligence. The National Education Policy of 2020 (NEP 2020) recognized the immense potential of AI and recommended its integration into the education system. To increase technology integration in schools, the CBSE in October last year introduced Artificial Intelligence (AI) and the Internet of Things (IoT) in the school curriculum from classes VI to X. AI has the potential to transform education by making it more efficient, effective, and accessible to students worldwide. However experts say it is crucial to ensure that the use of AI in education is ethical and responsible, and that it complements the work of human teachers rather than replacing them. 

Guests: 
1. Prof. M Jagadesh Kumar, Chairman, University Grants Commission
2. Prof. Dinesh Prasad Saklani, Director, NCERT

recommandationVideos.Title: Kaukopartioreissu Petrovski Jamiin
recommandationVideos.Description:
Suomalaiset kaukopartiomiehet tekivät jatkosodan aikana  tiedustelumatkoja, mutta myös tuhoamispartiota lähetettiin aika ajoin vihollispuolelle. Yksi kaukopartiomiesten kuuluisimmista tuhoamisretkistä oli 8. – 16. helmikuuta 1942, tuolla reissulla tuhottiin Petrovski Jamin huoltokeskus. Tätä operaatiota pidetään Suomen kaukopartiotoiminnan yhtenä suurimmista onnistumisista ja se tuli täytenä yllätyksenä Puna-armeijalle. Tämä Maaselän kannaksen suurin huoltokeskus perustettiin vuoden 1942 alussa Uikujärven ja Uikujoen rannalle Petrovski Jam nimiseen kylään. Sen verran asia koskettaa minuakin, sillä Karhumäestä kotoisin ollut Aleksanteri pyysi minua kesällä 2018 Lumbusin, Voljärven ja Uikujärven alueelle etsimään kadonneita suomalaisvainajia, mutta ne hommat minun kohdalta oli jätettävä nuoremmille miehille. Hän oli kuullut sinä keväällä julkaisemastani Taistellen Karhumäkeen nimisestä kirjasta, siinä käsittelin Karhumäen, Povetsan, Voljärven ja Malun rintamien tapahtumia tammi-helmikuussa 1942.  Naapurikylässä, muutaman kilometrin päässä asuinpaikastani, asui aiemmin Mannerheim-ristin ritari Onni Määttänen, joka oli myös tällä Petrovski Jam reissulla mukana. Petrovski Jam reissulla oli myös muita Mannerheim-ristin ritareiksi myöhemmin nimitettyjä partiomiehiä.

recommandationVideos.Description:
Jalkaväkirykmentti 9. perustettiin kesäkuussa 1941 Kontiolahdessa 9. prikaatin varusmiehistä ja Pohjois-Karjalan suojeluskuntapiirin reservijoukoista. Rykmentti liitettiin eversti Antero Svenssonin 7. divisioonaan yhdessä jalkaväkirykmenttien 30 ja 51 kanssa. 
Karjalan Armeijan joukko-osastot etenivät valtakunnanrajan yli vanhaan Suomen karjalaan 10. heinäkuuta kello 17.00 alkaen. Eteneminen vanhan Suomen Karjalan alueella jatkui rankkojen taistelujen saattelemana aina Sortavalaan saakka, jonne saavuttiin 15. elokuuta 1941.
Etenemistä jatkettiin 23. elokuuta Koivuselkään ja siletä edelleen Uomaan kylään. Elokuun lopussa 1941 rykmentti ylitti vanhan rajan Käsnäselän ja Kolatselän välissä. Jalkaväkirykmentti yhdeksän taisteli syyskuussa Aunukseen kuuluvissa Nirkan, Pyhäjärven, Kaskanan ja Latvan erämaissa lokakuun alkuun saakka. 
Syvärin joki ylitettiin 6. lokakuuta 1941 kolmannella yrityskerralla. Marraskuussa 1941 eteneminen päättyi Ostan, Goran ja Horomovitsin linjalle. Näissä asemissa Jalkaväkirykmentti yhdeksän oli kesään 1944 saakka.
Tällä videolla kerron kesän ja syksyn 1941 JR 9:n taisteluista Tohmajärveltä aina Syvärin taakse Levinaan ja Baranyn takaisiin kyliin saakka.  Lähteenä tällä videolla olen käyttänyt sotapäiväkirjoja ja kolmea 2010-luvulla tekemiäni sotakirjoja. Kirjojen tekemisen taustalla oli isäni ja hänen neljä veljeä, jotka palvelivat koko sodan ajan Jalkaväkirykementti yhdeksän eri pataljoonissa.
Isäni toimi jatkosodan aikana II/JR 9 konekiväärimiehenä. Hänen esimiehenä oli lähes koko sodan ajan Mannerheim-ristin ritari Ahti Vuorensola.

recommandationVideos.Title: India's Infra Thrust To Ladakh: Countering China & Pakistan
recommandationVideos.Description:
India’s military is in the fourth winter of its advanced forward deployment against China’s People’s Liberation Army (PLA) forces along the Line of Actual Control (LAC) in eastern Ladakh. China’s renewed aggression in 2020 led to the deadly Galwan clashes in June that year, with the consequent military buildup and standoff. Both sides continue to engage at the military, diplomatic and political level. But the shattering of trust, protocols and agreements means India is on perpetual guard in the present while ramping up its preparedness for the future.

StratNews Global’s team of Amitabh P. Revi, Rohit Pandita and Karan Marwaha travels along alpine altitudes through the frozen desert landscape in eastern Ladakh and Siachen to bring you this series: The Himalayan Frontier. These ground reports document the sustained infrastructure push in road connectivity and air bridges, record substantial progress in alternate axes that are in play and are being planned, and capture on camera how the Indian Army, the Border Roads Organisation (BRO) and the Indian Air Force’s women, men and machines are honing their all-weather readiness during another winter, against the two-front threat from China and Pakistan.

In this episode, we travel from Manali, through the Atal Tunnel under the Rohtang Pass and drive on the Darcha-Padam-Nimmu (NPD) road to Leh. This is a crucial third axis to Leh that will ensure all-weather connectivity for India's military and civilians, even when upto fifteen foot high snow walls usually close passes as high as 17,000  feet for months in the winter. The Border Roads Organisation (BRO) is the nodal agency for this infrastructural push and we travel with their personnel to understand their engineering achievements through bone-chilling alpine altitudes, how they drill through mountain ranges, lay bridges across fast-moving rivers and the challenges at these heights, temperatures and topographies.

recommandationVideos.Title: Heart disease press release
recommandationVideos.Description:
Our world in data excess mortality

https://ourworldindata.org/grapher/excess-mortality-p-scores-average-baseline?country=~JPN

Early heart disease deaths rise to 14-year high
 
Over 100,000 excess deaths involving cardiovascular conditions in England since February 2020

Heart and circulatory diseases cause around a quarter of all deaths in England,

Over 140,000 deaths each year,

or one death every four minutes.

Healthcare costs relating to heart and circulatory diseases, £8.3 billion each year.

The cost of cardiovascular disease to the wider economy in England,

(including premature death, disability and informal costs),

is estimated to be £22 billion each year.

Latest NHS England figures show that the number of people waiting for cardiac care at the end of November in England was 402,208.

The heart care waiting list is 72% larger than in February 2020. 

This is an increase of 169,000 people – enough to fill Wembley stadium nearly twice over.

In 2022

Over 39,000 people in England died prematurely of cardiovascular conditions,

heart attacks, coronary heart disease and stroke,

an average of 750 people each week. 

It is the highest annual total since 2008.
 
Since 2020, the premature death rate for cardiovascular disease has risen year-on-year

This is the first time there has been a clear reversal in the trend for almost 60 years.
 
The BHF says more analysis is needed to understand what is driving the trend. 

Dr Sonya Babu-Narayan, Associate Medical Director at the BHF and Consultant Cardiologist, said: 

We are still seeing more people than expected die from cardiovascular conditions overall – more than any other disease group. 

It’s clear to me that urgent intervention is long overdue.
 
In January 2023, the Government announced a Major Conditions Strategy to tackle the biggest drivers of ill health and early death in England

Other senior party figures immediately hit back, urging colleagues to “unite and get on with the job”.

Chief political commentator Peter Cardwell brands the Tory civil war as a "farce", as an ex-ally tells MPs to oust Sunak as PM.

recommandationVideos.Title: #DelhiWinterEmergency: Man on mission to save the homeless says ‘found 27 dead so far’
recommandationVideos.Description:
#delhiwinter 

Delhi is freezing, with temperatures dipping to as low as 3 degrees, proving to be fatal for the poor and homeless in the national capital. 

And since 2017, Vicky Sharma, 33, has hit the city's roads every night during winter to help those without shelter. He roams around, finding those who sleep on the cold bare floor, without anything warm on them, those that face the winter with a cotton sheet, and covers them with blankets.

Sharma, who was once homeless himself, is the general secretary of the Delhi Shelter Home Workers’ Union. “We rescue at least 50 people everyday. Since November 15, we have picked up 27 bodies of those who have died of cold on the road.” 

Sharma has no family and used to live at Patel Chowk metro station till December 2014. He then began working as a caretaker at the Delhi government-run night shelters. Moving around in an ambulance van, donated to him by social activist Sunil Kumar Aledia, Sharma usually helps people in the Old Delhi area.  

Aledia says 76 people are known to have died from cold between December 23 and January 5. 

Every year, Sharma and his team of four to five people – most of them previously homeless – find the bodies of at least 60-70 people who succumbed to the cold. “In January, the cold peaks and more people pass away. This year, we expect more people to die as there are not enough shelters and government aid,” he said.

recommandationVideos.Title: Why The World Is Rushing Back To The Moon
recommandationVideos.Description:
During the Cold War, competition between the the United States and the former USSR was fierce, as the two countries rallied for the chance to make history by getting to the moon first. In 1959, the Soviet Union beat the U.S. to become the first nation to reach the surface of the moon with its Luna 2 spacecraft. But, the United States was the first country to put man on the moon in 1969, and to this day is still the only nation to have landed people on the moon. To date, only five nations, the U.S., Russia, China, Japan and India, have completed a successful soft landing on the moon. But bolstered by evidence of the presence of water and other natural resources, many more nations and private companies are now seeking to get to the moon. And whoever is able to establish a significant lunar presence first could have big implications on Earth as well as the cosmos.

recommandationVideos.Title: #DelhiWinterEmergency: Man on mission to save the homeless says ‘found 27 dead so far’
recommandationVideos.Description:
#delhiwinter 

Delhi is freezing, with temperatures dipping to as low as 3 degrees, proving to be fatal for the poor and homeless in the national capital. 

And since 2017, Vicky Sharma, 33, has hit the city's roads every night during winter to help those without shelter. He roams around, finding those who sleep on the cold bare floor, without anything warm on them, those that face the winter with a cotton sheet, and covers them with blankets.

Sharma, who was once homeless himself, is the general secretary of the Delhi Shelter Home Workers’ Union. “We rescue at least 50 people everyday. Since November 15, we have picked up 27 bodies of those who have died of cold on the road.” 

Sharma has no family and used to live at Patel Chowk metro station till December 2014. He then began working as a caretaker at the Delhi government-run night shelters. Moving around in an ambulance van, donated to him by social activist Sunil Kumar Aledia, Sharma usually helps people in the Old Delhi area.  

Aledia says 76 people are known to have died from cold between December 23 and January 5. 

Every year, Sharma and his team of four to five people – most of them previously homeless – find the bodies of at least 60-70 people who succumbed to the cold. “In January, the cold peaks and more people pass away. This year, we expect more people to die as there are not enough shelters and government aid,” he said.

recommandationVideos.Title: India's Infra Thrust To Ladakh: Countering China & Pakistan
recommandationVideos.Description:
India’s military is in the fourth winter of its advanced forward deployment against China’s People’s Liberation Army (PLA) forces along the Line of Actual Control (LAC) in eastern Ladakh. China’s renewed aggression in 2020 led to the deadly Galwan clashes in June that year, with the consequent military buildup and standoff. Both sides continue to engage at the military, diplomatic and political level. But the shattering of trust, protocols and agreements means India is on perpetual guard in the present while ramping up its preparedness for the future.

StratNews Global’s team of Amitabh P. Revi, Rohit Pandita and Karan Marwaha travels along alpine altitudes through the frozen desert landscape in eastern Ladakh and Siachen to bring you this series: The Himalayan Frontier. These ground reports document the sustained infrastructure push in road connectivity and air bridges, record substantial progress in alternate axes that are in play and are being planned, and capture on camera how the Indian Army, the Border Roads Organisation (BRO) and the Indian Air Force’s women, men and machines are honing their all-weather readiness during another winter, against the two-front threat from China and Pakistan.

In this episode, we travel from Manali, through the Atal Tunnel under the Rohtang Pass and drive on the Darcha-Padam-Nimmu (NPD) road to Leh. This is a crucial third axis to Leh that will ensure all-weather connectivity for India's military and civilians, even when upto fifteen foot high snow walls usually close passes as high as 17,000  feet for months in the winter. The Border Roads Organisation (BRO) is the nodal agency for this infrastructural push and we travel with their personnel to understand their engineering achievements through bone-chilling alpine altitudes, how they drill through mountain ranges, lay bridges across fast-moving rivers and the challenges at these heights, temperatures and topographies.

recommandationVideos.Title: Heart disease press release
recommandationVideos.Description:
Our world in data excess mortality

https://ourworldindata.org/grapher/excess-mortality-p-scores-average-baseline?country=~JPN

Early heart disease deaths rise to 14-year high
 
Over 100,000 excess deaths involving cardiovascular conditions in England since February 2020

Heart and circulatory diseases cause around a quarter of all deaths in England,

Over 140,000 deaths each year,

or one death every four minutes.

Healthcare costs relating to heart and circulatory diseases, £8.3 billion each year.

The cost of cardiovascular disease to the wider economy in England,

(including premature death, disability and informal costs),

is estimated to be £22 billion each year.

Latest NHS England figures show that the number of people waiting for cardiac care at the end of November in England was 402,208.

The heart care waiting list is 72% larger than in February 2020. 

This is an increase of 169,000 people – enough to fill Wembley stadium nearly twice over.

In 2022

Over 39,000 people in England died prematurely of cardiovascular conditions,

heart attacks, coronary heart disease and stroke,

an average of 750 people each week. 

It is the highest annual total since 2008.
 
Since 2020, the premature death rate for cardiovascular disease has risen year-on-year

This is the first time there has been a clear reversal in the trend for almost 60 years.
 
The BHF says more analysis is needed to understand what is driving the trend. 

Dr Sonya Babu-Narayan, Associate Medical Director at the BHF and Consultant Cardiologist, said: 

We are still seeing more people than expected die from cardiovascular conditions overall – more than any other disease group. 

It’s clear to me that urgent intervention is long overdue.
 
In January 2023, the Government announced a Major Conditions Strategy to tackle the biggest drivers of ill health and early death in England

recommandationVideos.Title: Why SEBI Settles With Corrupt Stock Market Players? | Settlement Process
Keywords: types of settlement in stock market
settlement of trade in stock market
clearing and settlement in stock market
sebi regulations violation in stock market
recommandationVideos.Description:
In 2023, SEBI settled with 58 different companies for a total of 110 Crores. But what is this settlement? A settlement occurs when a company, having breached any of SEBI's regulations and earned money as a result, undergoes an investigation by SEBI. In response, the company submitted a proposal to SEBI expressing its intention to settle the matter. This proposal includes an amount that the company is willing to pay to SEBI, and, in exchange, SEBI agrees not to pursue further investigation in the case.

This rule from SEBI has been adopted from the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, where similar settlements are routinely reached with major companies. 

In this video, we will know the complete process of such settlements, exploring how they unfold. Additionally, we will discuss how these settlements assist in addressing frauds or regulatory violations in the Indian stock market. What role does settlement play in such cases, and what are the consequences for companies if a settlement is not reached? 

In December 2023, there were 8 cases, and in March 2023, there were 9 cases, making a total of 58 cases throughout the year. These cases involved a range of entities, from small to large companies, including investment firms, listed companies, stock brokers, exchanges, Finfluencers, and international banks. Collaboratively, settlements totaling up to 110 crore were reached.

The settlements primarily revolved around cases related to insider trading, which is prohibited in India. Whenever a company engages in insider trading, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) becomes prepared to make settlements. Also there are numerous other regulations that, when violated, lead to settlements being made.

However, it's not necessary that every time only settlements happen; many times penalties are also imposed. Till now, SEBI has settled in 1775 cases, making it difficult to estimate the total amount involved.

In those cases where settlements occur, SEBI collects a sum of money from those who have violated regulations. But nothing is done to address the significant losses faced by traders and investors in these cases. While SEBI takes action against those breaking the Regulations by settlement, there is often no compensation for the financial losses experienced by traders and investors.

SEBI has been saying for a long time that it is establishing rules and regulations to deal with fraud and those who break them. Sebi negotiates with those who violate regulations and make millions and crores of rupees through these settlements. However, SEBI should also take steps for traders or investors who have genuinely suffered losses, so that their losses can be recovered.

To gain a better understanding of the settlement process, watch the entire video.

recommandationVideos.Title: Traders don't need to Transfer Money to Broker | ASBA for Secondary Market, SEBI New Rule
recommandationVideos.Description:
Over the past 5 years, 18 stockbrokers including Bezel, Action Financial, Anugrah, Karvy, and Vrise have defaulted, all for the same reason—misappropriation of their clients' funds. 

SEBI consistently believes that brokers misuse clients' funds when they have excess access to them. Therefore, a solution is needed to ensure that the broker does not have unfettered access to the client's funds. Just as the ASBA (Application Supported by Blocked Amount) system was introduced for applying in IPOs in the primary market in 2019, a similar mechanism should be implemented for certain transactions in the secondary market.

In this video, we will explore why the ASBA system is being considered and its positive aspects. We will also discuss the potential risks associated with it and analyze the benefits and positive sides it brings to the table.

Application Supported by Blocked Amount (ASBA) is a financial mechanism that simplifies the process of applying for shares or securities during an Initial Public Offering (IPO) or a rights issue. It ensures that investors don't have to transfer the entire application amount upfront, providing a more secure and controlled method for handling funds.

In simple terms, when you want to invest in a new stock offering, rather than paying the full amount at the time of application, a specific amount equivalent to the application value is blocked in your bank account. This "blocked amount" remains in your account but is not accessible for any other transactions until the IPO or rights issue is completed.

ASBA works by linking your bank account with the application process. When you express interest in subscribing to new shares, the designated amount is temporarily set aside or "blocked" in your account. This ensures that you have the necessary funds to cover your investment, but it doesn't leave your account until the shares are allotted. If your application is successful, the blocked amount is utilised for payment, and if not, the amount is released back into your account.

ASBA provides a more efficient and secure way for investors to participate in new stock offerings without having to transfer funds in advance, offering a streamlined and controlled approach to managing financial transactions in the stock market.

Sebi wants to ensure that the ASBA facility is added, and traders do not directly add funds to their trading accounts with brokers. Instead, traders should utilize the ASBA facility through the brokerage app. They can use any online payment app to add the desired amount, and then proceed to block that amount through ASBA.

The funds will remain in the trader's bank account and will not be sent to the clearing corporation. The funds will only be transferred to the clearing corporation when the trader buys shares, using the ASBA facility, ensuring that the specified amount is sent to the clearing corporation only at the time of share purchase.

To learn more about this in detail watch our full video.

Sebi's New Rule - https://www.sebi.gov.in/legal/circulars/oct-2022/block-mechanism-in-demat-account-of-clients-undertaking-sale-transactions-clarification_64384.html

https://www.sebi.gov.in/legal/circulars/jan-2024/ease-of-doing-investments-by-investors-facility-of-voluntary-freezing-blocking-of-trading-accounts-by-clients_80597.html

recommandationVideos.Title: Why The World Is Rushing Back To The Moon
recommandationVideos.Description:
During the Cold War, competition between the the United States and the former USSR was fierce, as the two countries rallied for the chance to make history by getting to the moon first. In 1959, the Soviet Union beat the U.S. to become the first nation to reach the surface of the moon with its Luna 2 spacecraft. But, the United States was the first country to put man on the moon in 1969, and to this day is still the only nation to have landed people on the moon. To date, only five nations, the U.S., Russia, China, Japan and India, have completed a successful soft landing on the moon. But bolstered by evidence of the presence of water and other natural resources, many more nations and private companies are now seeking to get to the moon. And whoever is able to establish a significant lunar presence first could have big implications on Earth as well as the cosmos.

recommandationVideos.Title: Heart disease press release
recommandationVideos.Description:
Our world in data excess mortality

https://ourworldindata.org/grapher/excess-mortality-p-scores-average-baseline?country=~JPN

Early heart disease deaths rise to 14-year high
 
Over 100,000 excess deaths involving cardiovascular conditions in England since February 2020

Heart and circulatory diseases cause around a quarter of all deaths in England,

Over 140,000 deaths each year,

or one death every four minutes.

Healthcare costs relating to heart and circulatory diseases, £8.3 billion each year.

The cost of cardiovascular disease to the wider economy in England,

(including premature death, disability and informal costs),

is estimated to be £22 billion each year.

Latest NHS England figures show that the number of people waiting for cardiac care at the end of November in England was 402,208.

The heart care waiting list is 72% larger than in February 2020. 

This is an increase of 169,000 people – enough to fill Wembley stadium nearly twice over.

In 2022

Over 39,000 people in England died prematurely of cardiovascular conditions,

heart attacks, coronary heart disease and stroke,

an average of 750 people each week. 

It is the highest annual total since 2008.
 
Since 2020, the premature death rate for cardiovascular disease has risen year-on-year

This is the first time there has been a clear reversal in the trend for almost 60 years.
 
The BHF says more analysis is needed to understand what is driving the trend. 

Dr Sonya Babu-Narayan, Associate Medical Director at the BHF and Consultant Cardiologist, said: 

We are still seeing more people than expected die from cardiovascular conditions overall – more than any other disease group. 

It’s clear to me that urgent intervention is long overdue.
 
In January 2023, the Government announced a Major Conditions Strategy to tackle the biggest drivers of ill health and early death in England

recommandationVideos.Title: Why The World Is Rushing Back To The Moon
recommandationVideos.Description:
During the Cold War, competition between the the United States and the former USSR was fierce, as the two countries rallied for the chance to make history by getting to the moon first. In 1959, the Soviet Union beat the U.S. to become the first nation to reach the surface of the moon with its Luna 2 spacecraft. But, the United States was the first country to put man on the moon in 1969, and to this day is still the only nation to have landed people on the moon. To date, only five nations, the U.S., Russia, China, Japan and India, have completed a successful soft landing on the moon. But bolstered by evidence of the presence of water and other natural resources, many more nations and private companies are now seeking to get to the moon. And whoever is able to establish a significant lunar presence first could have big implications on Earth as well as the cosmos.

recommandationVideos.Title: Trump vence Nikki Haley em New Hampshire
recommandationVideos.Description:
Trump x Biden: como eleições nos EUA afetam investimentos lá fora em 2024?
Eleições nos Estados Unidos acendem grande debate político em 2024, mas como ficam os mercados - e o S&P500?
Na última segunda-feira (15), Donald Trump venceu uma das primeiras prévias do Partido Republicano, em Iowa, e segue bem-posicionado nas pesquisas para as eleições presidenciais dos Estados Unidos deste ano, com vantagem frente ao atual presidente, o democrata Joe Biden. No meio político, dos EUA e do mundo, o tema é prioridade em 2024. No mercado financeiro, é apenas mais um fato pontual deste ano.  
Gabriela Santos, do JPMorgan, afirma que o tema é de interesse do mercado, mas não é visto como motivo para mudanças na carteira de investimentos. A mudança dos juros pelo banco central, o Federal Reserve, é tido como mais significativo neste sentido.  
“Eleições presidenciais no Brasil e nos Estados Unidos são diferentes e tem um peso distinto nos mercados. Nos EUA, não há oscilação de um extremo ao outro com a mudança do presidente ou do Congresso. As instituições são fortes e oferecem segurança e estabilidade”, diz Santos, em painel do Onde Investir 2024, evento online gratuito do InfoMoney. 

Saiba mais:
